\subtree{
  \title{Reference photos — current PCB, unfilled locations, and rework issue}

  \p{Main PCB (Uncut Gem / Quantum Village / DEF CON 33): current clear photo of the bci.place-furnished board. Use it for board identity, connector-pad orientation, unfilled-footprint inspection, and incoming-condition reference only; it does not prove RF, optical, detector, ADC, or ODMR bring-up. The generated map is derived from the original GitHub KiCad/BOM sources (\code{plurigrid/UncutGem/hardware/PCB/Uncut Gem.kicad_pcb} and \code{Uncut Gem-BOM.csv}); the work table below controls whether each source footprint is populate-now, optional/DNP, verify-only, or leave-empty.}

  \image{hardware-builds/uncut-gem/current-photos/defcon33-main-pcb-clear-20260612.png}

  \image{hardware-builds/generated/uncut-gem-main-pcb-unfilled-locations.svg}

  \p{Current electronic issue: analog measurement integrity is the rework target. RF/modulation energy can couple into the detector-to-ADC path and make ODMR dips ambiguous. Capture stock dark, light, RF-off, RF-on, and sweep baselines before any rework; install the INA333 daughterboard only as a reversible improvement if the baseline confirms the issue.}

  \image{hardware-builds/generated/uncut-gem-adc-noise-rework.svg}

  \p{Repo DiamondMount assembly spec evidence is used only with current kit evidence for the prism, laser, and optical-mechanical work items below.}
}

